QUESTION 14 - THEORETICAL CALCULATION

Given:

F1 = 0.1P1² + 20P1 + 1.5

F2 = 0.1P2² + 30P2 + 1.9

Total Load Demand

P1 + P2 = 200 MW

--------------------------------------------------

1. Incremental Cost of Generator 1

dF1/dP1

= 0.2P1 + 20

--------------------------------------------------

2. Incremental Cost of Generator 2

dF2/dP2

= 0.2P2 + 30

--------------------------------------------------

3. Economic Dispatch Condition

dF1/dP1 = dF2/dP2

0.2P1 + 20

=

0.2P2 + 30

--------------------------------------------------

4. Rearranging

0.2P1 - 0.2P2 = 10

P1 - P2 = 50

--------------------------------------------------

5. Power Balance Equation

P1 + P2 = 200

--------------------------------------------------

6. Solving

P1 - P2 = 50

P1 + P2 = 200

------------------

2P1 = 250

P1 = 125 MW

--------------------------------------------------

7. Substitute in Power Balance

125 + P2 = 200

P2 = 75 MW

--------------------------------------------------

RESULT

Generator 1 Output

P1 = 125 MW

Generator 2 Output

P2 = 75 MW
